window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Butterflies animate our summers, but the 59 species found in the British Isles can be surprisingly elusive. Some bask unseen at the top of trees in London parks; others lurk at the bottom of damp bogs in Scotland.</p> <p>A few survive for months while other ephemeral creatures only fly for three days. Several are virtually extinct. Simon Shepherd reads this bewitching book charting Patrick Barkhamâ€™s quest to find each of them - from the Adonis Blue to the Dingy Skipper - in one unforgettable summer.</p>"; 
